interfaces.label: ElasticsearchApiToRedactInLogs
description: Definition of an API that should redact the requested body in the logs

children.label: path
description:
The ES path.
- If specified as a string, it'll be checked as `contains`.
- If specified as a RegExp, it'll be tested against the path.

children.label: method
description:
HTTP method.
If not provided, the path will be checked for all methods.

interfaces.label: ElasticsearchClientConfig
description: Configuration options to be used to create a {@link IClusterClient | cluster client}

interfaces.label: ElasticsearchConfigPreboot
description: A limited set of Elasticsearch configuration entries exposed to the `preboot` plugins at `setup`.

children.label: hosts
description:
Hosts that the client will connect to. If sniffing is enabled, this list will
be used as seeds to discover the rest of your cluster.

children.label: credentialsSpecified
description: Indicates whether Elasticsearch configuration includes credentials (`username`, `password` or `serviceAccountToken`).

interfaces.label: ElasticsearchRequestHandlerContext
description: Core's `elasticsearch` request handler context.

children.label: config
description: A limited set of Elasticsearch configuration entries.
signature: { readonly hosts: string[]; readonly credentialsSpecified: boolean; }

children.label: createClient
description: Create application specific Elasticsearch cluster API client with customized config. See {@link IClusterClient}.

children.label: type
description: Unique identifier of the client

children.label: clientConfig
description:
A config consists of Elasticsearch JS client options and
valid sub-set of Elasticsearch service config.
We fill all the missing properties in the `clientConfig` using the default
Elasticsearch config so that we don't depend on default values set and
controlled by underlying Elasticsearch JS client.
We don't run validation against the passed config and expect it to be valid.

children.label: setUnauthorizedErrorHandler
description:
Register a handler that will be called when unauthorized (401) errors are returned from any API
call to elasticsearch performed on behalf of a user via a {@link IScopedClusterClient | scoped cluster client}.

children.label: client
description: A pre-configured {@link IClusterClient | Elasticsearch client}

children.label: createClient
description: Create application specific Elasticsearch cluster API client with customized config. See {@link IClusterClient}.

children.label: type
description: Unique identifier of the client

children.label: clientConfig
description:
A config consists of Elasticsearch JS client options and
valid sub-set of Elasticsearch service config.
We fill all the missing properties in the `clientConfig` using the default
Elasticsearch config so that we don't depend on default values set and
controlled by underlying Elasticsearch JS client.
We don't run validation against the passed config and expect it to be valid.

description: Fake request object created manually by Kibana plugins.

interfaces.label: IClusterClient
description:
Represents an Elasticsearch cluster API client created by the platform.
It allows to call API on behalf of the internal Kibana user and
the actual user that is derived from the request headers (via `asScoped(...)`).

children.label: asScoped
description: Creates a {@link IScopedClusterClient | scoped cluster client} bound to given {@link ScopeableRequest | request}

interfaces.label: ICustomClusterClient
description: See {@link IClusterClient}

children.label: close
description:
Closes the cluster client. After that client cannot be used and one should
create a new client instance to be able to interact with Elasticsearch API.

children.label: healthCheckDelay
description: The interval between health check requests Kibana sends to the Elasticsearch.

children.label: ignoreVersionMismatch
description: Whether to allow kibana to connect to a non-compatible elasticsearch node.

children.label: apiVersion
description: Version of the Elasticsearch (6.7, 7.1 or `master`) client will be connecting to.

children.label: maxSockets
description: The maximum number of sockets that can be used for communications with elasticsearch.

children.label: maxIdleSockets
description: The maximum number of idle sockets to keep open between Kibana and Elasticsearch. If more sockets become idle, they will be closed.

children.label: idleSocketTimeout
description: The timeout for idle sockets kept open between Kibana and Elasticsearch. If the socket is idle for longer than this timeout, it will be closed.

children.label: compression
description: Whether to use compression for communications with elasticsearch.

children.label: hosts
description:
Hosts that the client will connect to. If sniffing is enabled, this list will
be used as seeds to discover the rest of your cluster.

children.label: requestHeadersWhitelist
description:
List of Kibana client-side headers to send to Elasticsearch when request
scoped cluster client is used. If this is an empty array then *no* client-side
will be sent.

children.label: pingTimeout
description: Timeout after which PING HTTP request will be aborted and retried.

children.label: requestTimeout
description: Timeout after which HTTP request will be aborted and retried.

children.label: shardTimeout
description: Timeout for Elasticsearch to wait for responses from shards. Set to 0 to disable.

children.label: sniffOnStart
description:
Specifies whether the client should attempt to detect the rest of the cluster
when it is first instantiated.

children.label: sniffInterval
description:
Interval to perform a sniff operation and make sure the list of nodes is complete.
If `false` then sniffing is disabled.

children.label: sniffOnConnectionFault
description:
Specifies whether the client should immediately sniff for a more current list
of nodes when a connection dies.

children.label: username
description:
If Elasticsearch is protected with basic authentication, this setting provides
the username that the Kibana server uses to perform its administrative functions.
Cannot be used in conjunction with serviceAccountToken.

children.label: password
description:
If Elasticsearch is protected with basic authentication, this setting provides
the password that the Kibana server uses to perform its administrative functions.

children.label: serviceAccountToken
description:
If Elasticsearch security features are enabled, this setting provides the service account
token that the Kibana server users to perform its administrative functions.

This is an alternative to specifying a username and password.

children.label: customHeaders
description:
Header names and values to send to Elasticsearch with every request. These
headers cannot be overwritten by client-side headers and aren't affected by
`requestHeadersWhitelist` configuration.

children.label: ssl
description:
Set of settings configure SSL connection between Kibana and Elasticsearch that
are required when `xpack.ssl.verification_mode` in Elasticsearch is set to
either `certificate` or `full`.

children.label: apisToRedactInLogs
description: Extends the list of APIs that should be redacted in logs.

interfaces.label: IScopedClusterClient
description:
Serves the same purpose as the normal {@link IClusterClient | cluster client} but exposes
an additional `asCurrentUser` method that doesn't use credentials of the Kibana internal
user (as `asInternalUser` does) to request Elasticsearch API, but rather passes HTTP headers
extracted from the current user request to the API instead.

children.label: asInternalUser
description:
A {@link ElasticsearchClient | client} to be used to query the elasticsearch cluster
on behalf of the internal Kibana user.
